https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-amazon/
https://docs.aws.amazon.com/dms/latest/sbs/chap-mongodb2documentdb.02.html

Install mongodb 7
sudo vi /etc/yum.repos.d/mongodb-org-7.0.repo
sudo yum install -y mongodb-org
# sudo yum install -y mongodb-org-7.0.5 mongodb-org-database-7.0.5 mongodb-org-server-7.0.5 mongodb-mongosh-7.0.5 mongodb-org-mongos-7.0.5 mongodb-org-tools-7.0.5
sudo systemctl start mongod
sudo systemctl enable mongod
sudo systemctl status mongod
its data files in /var/lib/mongo
its log files in /var/log/mongodb
Start a mongosh session on the same host machine as the mongod. You can run mongosh without any command-line options to connect to a mongod that is running on your localhost with default port 27017.

Uninstall MongoDB
Stop MongoDB.
Stop the mongod process by issuing the following command:
sudo service mongod stop
Remove Packages.
Remove any MongoDB packages that you had previously installed.
sudo yum erase $(sudo rpm -qa | grep mongodb-org)
Remove Data Directories.
Remove MongoDB databases and log files.
sudo rm -r /var/log/mongodb
sudo rm -r /var/lib/mongo
